This week we hosted our Annual Culture Awards, recognizing the achievements of people from across the firm who embody the spirit and values that make us uniquely Edelman. Please join us in congratulating the individuals and teams who won Culture Awards this year!
 
The awards are:
 
💙 The Freedom to be Constantly Curious: Recognizes an employee whose commitment to continuous improvement, diversity of thought and creativity has led to growth for a client or Edelman.
 
💙 The Courage to do the Right Thing: Recognizes an employee who has exhibited integrity and strong leadership promoting a positive and fair work environment for themselves, their colleagues, the clients, and/or their community.
 
💙 The Commitment to Positively Impact Society: Recognizes an employee who upholds the highest level of standards for the communities in which they live and work, and performs their work with a sense of tolerance, fairness and equality.
 
💙 The Relentless Pursuit of Excellence: Recognizes an employee who exemplifies excellence in the way they service clients, respect ideas that promote equity and fairness, and/or support their colleagues.
 
💙 The Charles E. Fremes IQ Heroes: Recognizes employees who have created new processes, products, and offerings that have measurably improved the overall quality of our work and strengthened our client relationships.
 
💙 The Dario Iannucci La Dolce Vita Award: Recognizes employees who exemplify Dario’s spirit of partnership and care and exhibit integrity and strong leadership promoting a positive, fair, and equitable work environment.
 
💙 The Ruth Edelman Citizenship Award: Recognizes the citizenship project (pro bono or internal sustainability) that best demonstrates Edelman’s commitment to positively impact society.

Did you know? Prostate cancer is the second most common cancer in men - but when caught early, the 5-year survival rate is over 99%!

Our colleague Brien Ott recently faced a prostate cancer diagnosis. Thanks to his wife and his care team, Brien was able to get a diagnosis and treatment quickly. When he got the news that he was facing prostate cancer, his care team was able to act quickly through MRI imaging, a biopsy, and eventually treatment. With GE HealthCare’s portfolio of tools—from imaging to patient monitoring—Brien saw his life’s work come full circle and experience the true value of connected oncology care that empowers both patients and healthcare teams.

Here’s to supporting the entirety of the patient journey and enabling early diagnosis when it matters most! 💜

In the weeks leading up to the Paris Olympic trials, British rower @george.bourne was challenged by a COVID-19 diagnosis that raised heart health concerns. Following cardiac issues among some teammates, he consulted Dr. Sanjay Sharma, a top sports cardiologist in the UK.

Now cleared, George is eager to continue his rowing journey. 💜

Today is #WorldLungCancerDay, a day dedicated to raising awareness and supporting those affected by this disease.

At @GEHealthCare, we're committed to advancing lung cancer detection and treatment. But how much do you know about this critical health issue? We've compiled some facts that might surprise you:

1 - Lung cancer is the leading cause of cancer deaths worldwide.

2 - Low-dose CT scans can be used for lung cancer screening.

3 - Exposure to radon or wood smoke are risk factors for lung cancer.

4 - There are AI-powered tools to help detect and manage lung nodules.

At only 19, @astro_johnmcfall's life took a dramatic turn when he lost his leg, altering his military ambitions. Little did he know, however, what life had in store…

He later went on to become a Paralympian medalist and is now poised to be the first astronaut with a physical disability in the professional space program.

Dr. Martin Bansmann, a radiology professor at the German Hospital Porz am Rhein collaborating with @europeanspaceagency, has the extensive task of making sure prospects like McFall are physically ready for space. Dr. Bansmann's groundbreaking work in medical imaging and aerospace medicine has helped set the standard for evaluating ESA astronauts and German Air Force pilots.

Advanced medical imaging technologies like MRI, CT scans, X-rays, and ultrasound technologies, provide detailed insights into organ systems, enabling healthcare professionals to assess overall health status. Enhanced by artificial intelligence, these systems enable clinicians to meticulously detect even the minutest irregularities, ensuring peak health and performance in the most demanding environments. 🚀

Discover more about this inspiring story via the link in our bio. 🔗

#FutureofHealthcare #SpaceExploration #MedicalTechnology

Craftolution ~ What makes an Iris van Herpen design move the way it moves?
Having practiced classical ballet from a young age, Iris has learned about the transformation of the body and experiences dance as one of the most influential things in her life. This awareness of living, breathing gestures have become part of her Design DNA and each new creation starts with an elaborate R&D process where materials and forms are pushed to their limits, through which the fluidity of movement is relentlessly tested and experimented with. This evolution of craftsmanship she refers to as ‘craftolution’ and makes each design a dynamic ‘living’ extension of the human form.  

The Fractal Flows look is made with sound waves that were live-painted and filmed by the artist Perry Hall to then be transparently printed onto glass-organza spheres. The hundreds of patterned spheres were then multilayered and heatbonded to 3D lasercut dendrites of black cotton, to create waves that arc the body ‘medusoidly’.

#irisvanherpen #hautecouture

For over 27 years, Children’s Harbor has been providing a harbor of hope and healing right here in our South Florida community for children who have been impacted by the trauma of child abuse.

Children’s Harbor’s mission is powerful:

We Keep Kids Safe.
Our main campus provides a family environment to teenagers in foster care and their younger siblings.

We Help Families Heal.
Our Family Strengthening team prevents kids from coming into foster care by providing in-house counseling and support to families who are struggling in our community.

We Shine a Light Toward Hope.
Our independent living programs provide support and wrap-around guidance to teens who have aged out of the foster care system through the early stages of adulthood.

National Geographic photographers ventured to places far and wide to capture the year’s most fascinating images. Out of more than 2.3 million photos, 20 were selected as our Pictures of the Year. See them all at the link in bio.

📸 1 - @amivitale photographed a 70-day-old fetus of a rhino conceived through in vitro fertilization. In January, scientists announced that they had for the first time achieved a pregnancy after using IVF to transfer a southern white rhino embryo into a southern white rhino surrogate. But before scientists could confirm the pregnancy, the surrogate mother died from an unrelated bacterial infection. A necropsy revealed that she was pregnant. While the moment was “heartbreaking,” Ami Vitale says, it proved that IVF is viable in rhinos. The team has plans to try again in early 2025, this time transferring a northern white rhino embryo into a southern white rhino surrogate. Vitale’s work documenting steps to save northern white rhinos over the past 15 years is featured in “Explorer: Rhino Resurrection,” a forthcoming National Geographic film.

📸 2 - Davide Monteleone (@davidemonteleonestudio) photographed liquid fuel from the sun. Made using sunlight, water, and carbon dioxide, this solar synthetic fluid has the potential to replace fossil fuels. It could be used to power trucks, ships, and planes without retrofitting. In June, Swiss company Synhelion opened the world’s first industrial-scale plant to produce the energy alternative.

📸 3 - @johnstanmeyer documented a centuries-old love song. Periodical cicadas, which spend 13 or 17 years in the ground, surface only to reproduce. Last May and June, for the first time in 221 years, brood XIII, with a 17-year cycle, and brood XIX, with a 13-year cycle, emerged simultaneously in the Midwest and southeastern United States, respectively, filling the air with vibrations as they called out to mate.

(ad) Comment ‘RECIPE’ to have this Mochi Cake with @nutella recipe sent to your DMs 💌 Creamy @nutella is served on a slice of this buttery, chewy cake for a perfect movie night treat.

Mochi cake is a type of dessert made with glutinous rice flour (also known as sweet rice flour), giving it a unique, chewy texture that’s characteristic of mochi. Unlike traditional cakes that are soft and crumbly, mochi cake is dense, slightly springy, and stretchy due to the glutinous rice flour.

INGREDIENTS:
1 lb glutinous rice flour
1 tsp kosher salt
1.5 tsp baking powder
1/2 cup butter (1 stick) softened to room temp
2 cups sugar
3 eggs, room temp
1.5 tsp vanilla extract
13.5 oz (1 can) coconut milk
butter or nonstick spray, for the pan
1 tbsp @nutella hazelnut spread, per serving

RECIPE:
1. In a mixing bowl, whisk together glutinous rice flour, salt, and baking powder. Set aside.
2. Use an electric mixer to cream the butter and sugar together.
3. Add eggs one at a time. Then, add vanilla extract and coconut milk.
4. Add the dry mixture and mix until well incorporated. No need to worry about over-mixing!
5. To prepare the pan, grease the pan with butter or nonstick spray. Line with parchment paper on the bottom, then grease the parchment paper.
6. Pour the batter into the pan. Tap the pan gently on the table to remove air bubbles.
7. Bake at 375 F for about 1 hr or until a toothpick runs clean and the top is golden brown. Let it cool for at least 30 minutes before serving.

🎥 by @itsforkandspoon

Kennedie Savage, an Oregon Ducks fan, didn’t let her wedding day stop her from watching her team’s game. 🏈👰‍♀️

During her Nov. 16 reception at Reber’s Riverside, Kennedie projected the Oregon Ducks vs. Wisconsin Badgers game onto her wedding dress.

Videographer Tyler Kinert captured the moment as Kennedie held her gown wide while cheering with guests. Initially unable to find a proper display spot in the barn, she jokingly said, “I’ll be the screen.” Guests loved the moment before the game was eventually moved to the barn wall.

The Ducks won 16-13, and the unique celebration gained attention online, with brands like Gatorade and Dr Pepper applauding her dedication to both her team and her big day.

Chinese researchers have reported early success with a novel surgical approach to treating Alzheimer’s. 😮🇨🇳

The procedure, described in General Psychiatry, aims to enhance the brain’s waste-clearing system by connecting lymphatic vessels in the neck to veins. This could help remove harmful proteins linked to the disease, such as beta-amyloid and tau.

Initial results from a patient showed slight improvements in cognitive scores and daily functioning within weeks. Brain scans also suggested changes in protein levels, though experts warn these findings are preliminary and need broader testing.

While this approach is not a cure and cannot reverse brain damage, it represents a step forward in Alzheimer’s research. It joins a wave of promising treatments, including drugs like donanemab and lecanemab, that aim to slow disease progression.

The NBA has advised players to upgrade their home security systems, consider guard dogs, and vet contractors after a series of burglaries targeting professional athletes. 🐕😮

Victims include Mike Conley of the Timberwolves, Bobby Portis of the Bucks, and NFL stars Travis Kelce and Patrick Mahomes.

In a memo obtained by ABC News, the league highlighted that many homes had alarms that were not activated. It also recommended removing real estate listings with home photos from public sites.

Authorities believe the burglaries are linked to sophisticated South American theft groups that use advanced tools like drones and signal jammers. The crimes often coincide with athletes’ game schedules, leaving homes unoccupied.

Credit card debt in the U.S. has hit a record $1.17 trillion, according to the Federal Reserve Bank of New York’s latest report. 📈💳

Balances rose by $24 billion in the third quarter of 2024, an 8.1% increase year-over-year. However, delinquency rates have improved slightly, with 8.8% of balances transitioning to delinquency, down from 9.1% in the previous quarter, suggesting that rising debt remains manageable.

Despite high borrowing costs, consumer spending remains strong. The average credit card balance per consumer is now $6,329, up 4.8% from last year, though the growth rate has slowed significantly compared to previous years.

Credit card interest rates remain above 20%, disproportionately impacting lower-income households struggling with inflation and high living costs. 

While potential Federal Reserve rate cuts could help ease borrowing costs, researchers emphasize that managing overall debt levels is more critical than changes in interest rates.

Mornings 🤝 Quaker oatmeal

Need a simple crowd pleaser for your Thanksgiving gathering? This oatmeal topped apple crisp is the perfect cozy recipe for the fall season. 🍎🍂
 
Filling: * 2 tbsp butter * 2 tbsp brown sugar * 5 whole pink lady apples (peeled and sliced)
 
Crumble: * 1/2 cup brown sugar * 1/2 cup flour * 1 cup Quaker® Oats-Old Fashioned * 1/2 tsp cinnamon * 1/3 tsp salt * 1/2 cup almonds * 1 stick butter melted * 1/2 tsp vanilla
 
Directions: 
Preheat oven to 350°F. Butter an 8-inch pie glass baking dish.
In a bowl toss apples, 2 tbsp of butter and brown sugar together. Pour apple mixture into pie glass baking dish and set aside.
In a medium bowl mix brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, cinnamon and salt together. Add almonds, butter and vanilla.
Mix with hands to bring mixture together.
Top your apple mixture with the oatmeal brown sugar mixture and place in the oven for 40 mins.
Remove from oven and serve with Greek yogurt, vanilla ice cream or eat on its own.

Starting January 1, 2025, all short-term rental accommodations (STRAs) in Muskoka Lakes will require a license to operate legally. This new bylaw is a significant step by the Muskoka Lakes council to balance tourism with community character and environmental protection.

In addition to ensuring properties are safe and compliant with regulations, the licensing program aims to address common concerns from Muskoka residents about short-term rentals. Mayor Peter Kelley expressed optimism that the bylaw will lead to fewer community issues, making Muskoka an even better place to live and visit.

For STRA operators, licensing will be an annual requirement, regardless of how long a property has been rented. To help rental operators prepare, the township is hosting a virtual webinar on December 10 at 10 a.m. via Eventbrite to go over the details of the licensing process. Applications will open in early 2025.

I have nothing personally against the Pacifier Fairy. She didn’t do me dirty or anything like that, but when I let myself think about it, it just feels like it cheapens the hard work that goes into eliminating the pacifier. It is OK for your child to know that this is going to be a hard thing and that they are doing it for nobody but themselves. 

If you have an infant, my Baby Sleep Basics Guide (for babies 4-18 months) goes over ways to eliminate the pacifier for a baby. It’s a much more straightforward thing. Otherwise, my Tackling Toddler Sleep Course (which is $20 off from now until November 30!) goes over all the ways to eliminate the pacifier (including the dang Fairy approach) and so does my Toddler Sleep Hacks book.

What you are going to have to do is prepare your child for the change by letting them know it is coming. I personally like to let them choose a date on a calendar and mark it off. I’m not sure why toddlers like calendars so much, but, have at it! Hype them up and talk about how they’re growing up and doing big things! I’d also let them know it may be a hard thing to do but they can do it! Sometimes, giving an alternate comfort object of their choosing can help ease the transition.

From there, on the day of eliminating the pacifier, have your child throw it away themselves! That’s it. No mythical being. 

Expect that there’ll be an adjustment period during which it’ll take your child longer to fall asleep. There are methods, strategies, and approaches for dealing with this while continuing to empower, support, and celebrate your child and their hard work! 

The getting rid of the pacifier isn’t the hard part, but sticking to it when it gets rough can be!

Check out TacklingToddlerSleep.com for my full toddler sleep course and ToddlerSleepHacks.com for my book! Both give you tools to help with this transition and you can be sure you’ll be setting your child (ages 2-5) up for success!

Sharing some more shameful parenting moments I was reminded of on my way to school. I think we need to be more honest and admit that we all do some incredible parenting. We also sometimes are mediocre. And sometimes we suck. I truly believe we can’t work on the sucky stuff until we acknowledge it. But we also need acknowledge it without berating ourselves.

Accepting that we have shortcomings or bad moments without chastising ourselves into the ground for it isn’t the same as giving ourselves a free pass for our less than perfect moments…but in my personal experience, I know that when I critique myself, I do it to an obsessive degree and it leaves no space for growth and doing better next time. But ALSO: we WILL MESS UP AGAIN EVEN IF WE HAVE REFLECTED FULLY! Because we are HUMAN BEINGS, NOT INSTAGRAM REELS.

I’m at a point in my parenting career where I am no longer trying to do things perfectly. I also strive to be a great parent, but I know damn well I am not perfect. And I don’t want to be. I admit that I am sh*tty AND I am great AND I am mediocre and I am ALL the things because I’m human and as Whitman once said “I contain multitudes.” 

I have strengths. I have weaknesses. I’ll keep doing my best, but some days, I may turn the volume up on the stereo when my kid cries and I’m gonna be ready to talk about how that was not the best course of action. 

I do have to note that “trauma” here is an overstatement and we should be more careful about how we use that word. There are some of us who truly are breaking cycles of trauma. This post isn’t meant to undermine that.

Happy Tuesday.

THIS IS NOT MEDICAL ADVICE.

If your toddler has used up every anti-sleep excuse and then they pull out the big g*ns and tell you they’re STARVING, you have a few options. I’m going to share with you the one that makes us as mothers feel better. There are other options in my Tackling Toddler Sleep course ($20 off until November 30), and in my Toddler Sleep Hacks book. 

Here it goes: 

Make a pre-bedtime snack part of your daily routine. 

This may mean something like, you eat dinner, take a bath, have a snack, and jump into the rest of bedtime routine. 

Listen, sometimes this can backfire for picky eaters because they rely on that pre-bedtime snack instead of the dinner that was served to them earlier. That is why, when taking this approach, I like to set parameters around what is served for the pre-bedtime snack. I personally like to make it something like yogurt and crackers or fruit, or peanut butter and apples, or something that feels a little bit more balanced (think a carb, fat, and protein) rather than just a carb on its own. They may not like what you’re offering, in which case, you may have to hold firm and let them know that’s what’s being offered and next meal is breakfast. 

I find that going this route helps the families I’ve worked with feel better about setting a boundary around bedtime because they feel more certain that their child is not actually hungry but is playing boundary pushing game. 

by the way, I am only kind of joking when I say you’re toddler is screwing with you. Normally, these extra requests are just a bid for attention and my book and course have you covered with how to fill up their cup emotionally as well!

if you want more information on this approach or other approaches in addition to ways to make bedtime fun  while teaching your child to sleep independently, check out TacklingToddlerSleep.com (for my course!) or ToddlerSleepHacks.com (for my book!)

Understanding the difference between personal injury and workers’ compensation can make a big difference in your recovery journey and the support you receive. Here’s a quick breakdown:

➡️ Personal Injury: Applies if you’re hurt outside of work (like in a car accident or at a store), and someone else may be at fault.

➡️ Workers’ Compensation: Covers injuries that happen on the job, regardless of fault, with medical and wage benefits.

Ever wonder why your watch just doesn’t seem to fit right? Here are 5 common reasons:

1. Wrong Strap Size: The strap might be too long or too short for your wrist. You could need a shorter or longer band for your watch to look and feel most comfortable on your wrist.

2. Improper Link Adjustment: Metal bands often need links removed or added to fit perfectly. It could be that your watch needs links removed or added. 

3. Stiff Material: Some watch bands are made of materials that don’t conform to your wrist. It could be that the material of your watch does not conform to your wrist comfortably. 

4. Incorrect Watch Placement: Wearing the watch too high or too low on your wrist can cause discomfort. It could be that your watch needs to be placed differently. 

5. Non-Adjustable Straps: Some watch bands lack the flexibility to adjust to different wrist sizes. It could be that you need watches with adjustable bands.

72 hours in Doha, Qatar felt like ten minutes. Doha is one of the all time greats. I barely scratched the surface of sights to see. One of the objectives was to meet students at the Doha Film Institute. They come from all over the world to study at DFI and grow into the next generation of filmmakers. 

We talked about failure, winning and the film business. We spoke about giving yourself permission to suck. You can’t be great at anything unless you’re first willing to “embrace  the suck”. Allowing yourself to be sloppy or wrong is a chance to play and experiment… a chance to lose and learn. Social media and the cult of perfectionism makes kids - and all of us - too hard on ourselves too soon. You can’t start at the finish line. I could have spent days talking to, learning from and teaching these students… thank you, @fatma_h_alremaihi and @dohafilm for making this possible. 

Also spoke at the Sportico summit with some heavy hitters. Topics swung wildly from technology to lower league football to Teletubbies. As expected. Thank you @sportico for putting this event together. Thank you, @erika for the excellent chat. And thanks to Doha, Qatar and my friends who are growing this magic place. Be back soon.

Are you an addict?

When you’re on first name terms with your delivery driver and your closet shelves are collapsing under the weight of all that polyester, it’s time for an intervention…

Fast Fashion Addiction Symptoms:

• Started thinking influencer haul videos are normal.
• Fell for fast fashion’s greenwashed ‘sustainability’ credentials.
• Impulse bought something ‘viral’ because you got fashion FOMO.
• Checked new arrivals pages daily just for something to do.
• Hit checkout on a trending style before you’ve even had a chance to think.

We’ve all been guilty of some of these. But when they become your shopping norm, you know you’ve got a problem. The good news is, there’s a way out. Whether you swap impulse buys for intentional purchases or replace your fast fashion scrolling with pre-loved resale sites, there’s plenty of little ways you can change your behaviours for the better.

#ThinkFirstBuySecond #FastFashionRedFlags

I used to be all about following the latest fashion trends, but now I’m more selective about what I buy for my closet. I’m investing in pieces that will last season to season to cause less overconsumption. And for that I’ll always start by shopping on @vestiaireco. 

#vestiairepartner#ThinkFirstBuySecond #SkeletonsInMyCloset #ChangeYourFeedChangeTheWorld

Imagine a world where getting your fashion fix comes guilt-free and at a fraction of the price. Sound too good to be true? Think again…

#ThinkFirstBuySecond #FastFashionRedFlags

What do we mean by overconsumption? Too much stuff. Too much speed. Too much waste.

And we’re being tricked into being complicit by the fast fashion giants and their clever marketing tactics. But it doesn’t have to be this way. From making more intentional purchases to clearing your feed from bad influences, every change–no matter how small–is a step towards a more sustainable future.

To help spread our message to the people with the power, we’ve invited influential content creators who’ve previously worked with fast fashion brands to join us on a 6-month educational program, including interactive masterclasses and a field trip to a clothing landfill site, to explore the ways we can all be a better influence.

As we find ourselves at the end of November, a month where Caregivers are celebrated – we want to recognize our colleagues who balance caring for a loved one with their professional lives. Informal care is indispensable in today’s society, with about 24% of employed people in the Netherlands combining their job with caregiving tasks.
 
At Ahold Delhaize, we create a caring place to work inspiring growth and collaboration, where everyone is heard, valued and finds purpose in serving our communities. This includes supporting associates through life’s transformative moments, like caring for a loved one.
 
This month, our Dutch brands introduced an informal caregiving policy to support associates with caregiving responsibilities. It aims to foster a workplace where colleagues can share challenges, receive managerial support, and access resources, including coaching, mental health support, leave options, sabbaticals, and remote working. The informal caregiving policy is part of our Life Events Framework, which integrates policies and tools to assist associates and guide managers.
 
#AholdDelhaize #caregiving

Before you board, read these safety tips to keep your journey hassle-free👇
🏅 Secure Your Valuables: Keep your valuables close and secure. Use a money belt or an anti-theft backpack to avoid pickpocketing.
👀 Stay Alert: Be aware of your surroundings, especially in busy stations and on crowded trains.
🕰️ Know Your Train Schedule: Check your train schedule and platform information ahead of time to avoid last-minute confusion.
🌅 Travel During Daylight: If possible, travel during daylight hours to enhance safety and visibility.
🔒 Use Luggage Locks: Lock your luggage to deter theft and keep it close to you when possible.
🗣️ Follow Local Advice: Pay attention to any safety notices or local advice given at train stations or on the train.
🌙 Be Cautious in Sleeper Trains: If traveling overnight, secure your belongings and choose a compartment with other passengers if possible.
💼 Avoid Displaying Wealth: Keep your wealth and electronics discreet to avoid drawing unwanted attention.
📱 Stay Connected: Keep your phone charged and have a backup power source to stay in touch and access travel information.

“Do menstrual discs hurt to use?” 

Heck NO they should never hurt! In fact, period discs are extremely comfortable. They’re so comfortable that 97% of surveyed disc users said they couldn’t feel them when they are wearing them. Many people actually forget that they’re on their period with a disc in. 🤯

Discs are so comfy because they sit in the  widest part of the vagina called the vaginal fornix (not in the vaginal canal like tampons or cups). The fornix has fewer nerve endings, so when a disc is placed there, you literally can’t even feel it. 

Disc users—share your experience on comfort in the comments! 👇

Curious? Try it for yourself! Buy online at flexfits.com or on Amazon, and in store at Walmart, Target, Walgreens, CVS...

#flexdisc #menstrualdisc #menstrualcup #menstrualcycle #period #menstrualhealth #womenshealth

If your disc is leaking, it’s probably not in correctly. Let’s troubleshoot…

Here are 3 common scenarios:

1. You nay not have pushed the disc back as far as you could, and its not at the base of your cervix.

2. The disc may have become unhooked from your pubic bone.

3. The disc may be sitting on top of your cervix, so its not capturing blood like it should.

To properly insert:
Pinch the disc, insert into your vaginal canal, push it down and back into your vaginal fornix, and secure it behind your pubic bone. Try wearing a liner or pad as you learn to properly insert your disc, for extra protection. 

And, please DM us or email help@Flexfits.com if you need more support. We are here for you! 🤝

Not all women menstruate and not all who menstruate are women. 🤍 

We understand that there may be some confusion, so let's clarify a few things together:

Firstly, it's important to acknowledge that not everyone who menstruates identifies as a woman. Transgender men and non-binary individuals, for example, can have uteruses and experience menstruation. Their gender identity is valid, and their experiences should be recognized and respected.

Additionally, it's important to remember that not all women menstruate. Some women may have undergone medical procedures, such as hysterectomies, where their uterus has been removed. This means they no longer experience menstruation. Their gender identity as women is still valid and should be respected.

Inclusivity means recognizing and embracing the diversity of human experiences fostering an environment of acceptance and understanding. It's about making space for everyone's experiences and dismantling harmful stereotypes.

Let's promote empathy and understanding for all people, regardless of their gender identity. 🌈🤍

Describe precision care in 10 seconds…⏱️ It sounds easy, but is it? We asked five of our leaders to define what it means to them.

Check out their insightful answers and share yours in the comments! 💡

#RSNA24

We had an unforgettable time at @rsnagram 2024! 

Watch our most memorable highlights.✨ 

#RSNA24

For 50 years, we’ve been at the forefront of computed tomography (CT) innovation. 

Let’s travel back to 1974 to see how our journey began… 

#RSNA24 #HistoryofInnovation #50YearsofCT #Innovation

RSNA 2024 is officially underway in Chicago, U.S.! 🎉 

Every year, the Radiological Society of North America brings together the brightest minds in medical imaging, and we’re excited to be part of it. 🌟 

Follow along to learn more about how we’re revolutionizing radiology with AI-enabled products and next-generation solutions. 💡 

#RSNA #RSNA24 @rsnagram

Only a decade ago, detecting amyloid plaques in Alzheimer’s patients required a post-mortem exam. Today, PET imaging allows radiologists to spot these plaques in living patients, sometimes even before symptoms appear. 🧠

Using an F18 radiotracer, PET scans can enable early diagnosis, treatment impact monitoring, and a better understanding of disease progression.

As the benefits of this procedure become more known, it’s important to ensure access is widely available to all patients—a challenge due to the cost-prohibitive nature and geographic availability of PET scans with precision diagnostics.

Read more on why investment in this breakthrough treatment matters at the link in our bio.

#HistoryofInnovation #AlzheimersDisease #FutureofHealthcare #PETImaging

We are pushing the boundaries of efficiency and capacity to benefit patients worldwide by adopting lean operations and accelerating the application of AI and digitalization 🌎

Our Beijing base has been recognized as a ‘Lighthouse Factory’ by the World Economic Forum—the first of its kind in China’s medical equipment industry and the second for GE HealthCare .

#LighthouseFactory #4IR #HealthcareInnovation

Healthcare should be closer to home! 💜

Initiatives like Care on Country help to break down barriers to healthcare by providing culturally respectful care to Australia’s First Nations people, allowing them to stay in their communities for essential services instead of relocating for treatment.

Earlier this year, our @gehealthcare team was honored to bring this model to life in Gapuwiyak, a remote town in Australia, where we provided critical imaging support to the community.

Let’s celebrate the power of healthcare that honors culture and keeps care where it belongs—close to home! 🇦🇺 🙌

#CareOnCountry #NationalRuralHealthMonth #InnovationInAction

As clinicians continue to leverage AI healthcare innovations, we’re showcasing several of these game-changing technologies at @rsnagram 2024.

From precision imaging to smarter workflows, these tools are shaping the future of patient care.

#RSNA24 #AI #HealthcareInnovation

Nearly half of radiologists are reporting burnout in a survey by the @rsnagram  Exams soared to 2.6 billion+ and the data captured is only increasing. Radiologists are overburdened and our technologies aim to address these challenges. 💜

Click on our link in bio to read more about some of the innovations that could enable providers to streamline workflows and provide more personalized care. 

#RSNA24

9 reasons your life is beautiful and worth living.
Life is beautiful because of the endless opportunities it offers for growth and self-discovery.

The beauty of nature, from colorful sunsets to majestic mountains, reminds us of the wonder and magic of life.

Relationships with family and friends bring love, support, and joy into our lives, making each day meaningful.

Achieving personal goals and dreams gives us a sense of accomplishment and purpose.

The ability to experience different cultures, foods, and traditions enriches our lives with diversity and new perspectives.

Moments of laughter, happiness, and shared memories create lasting bonds and treasured experiences.

Overcoming challenges and obstacles builds resilience and strength, showing us our own inner power.

Acts of kindness, generosity, and compassion towards others bring warmth and positivity to the world.

Each day is a new canvas to paint with opportunities, adventures, and possibilities, making life a beautiful journey worth living.

कल हो न हो, वीर जारा और दिल चाहता है जैसी तमाम फिल्मों के जरिए फैंस का दिल लूटने वाली डिंपल गर्ल प्रीति जिंटा सोशल मीडिया पर खूब एक्टिव रहती हैं. अपनी लाइफ से जुड़ी ज्यादातर बातें वो सोशल मीडिया पर शेयर करती रहती हैं. एक्ट्रेस ने बिजनेसमैन जीन गुडइनफ से शादी की है और साल 2021 में वो सेरोगेसी के जरिए दो जुड़वां बच्चों की मां बनी थीं. हालांकि अभी तक उन्होंने अपने बच्चों का चेहरा रिवील नहीं किया है, लेकिन उनके साथ फोटोज अक्सर शेयर करती रहती हैं. हाल ही में प्रीति ने अपने बेटे जय की एक मजेदार फोटो शेयर की है.

इन फोटोज में देखा जा सकता है कि जय अपनी नानी के साथ किच�� में खड़े हैं और उनके हाथ में बेलन है. नानी जय को रोटियां बनाना सिखा रही हैं और वो बड़ी दिलचस्पी से उनको देख रहे हैं. एक फोटो में वो रोटी बनाने की कोशिश करते भी दिख रहे हैं. फोटो पोस्ट करते हुए कैप्शन में प्रीति जिंटा ने लिखा, “जिंदगी में सबसे अच्छी चीज है फ्री. जैसे कि नानी मां और हमारे छोटे शेफ जय के हाथ से बनी रोटी खाने की खुशी. सभी को हैप्पी संडे.”

इंदौर के डीसीपी विनोद मीणा ने कहा कि आम तौर पर देखा जाता है कि गंभीर अपराधों शामिल बदमाशों की तलाश चल रही है. हजारों रुपयों का इनाम भी घोषित किया गया है. जिसके कारण बदमाश खुद को बड़ा बदमाश बताते हैं. उन्होंने कहा कि बदमाशों पर जितना अधिक इनाम घोषित किया जाता है वो अपना उतना ही खौफ स्थापित करते हैं और खुद को बड़ा बदमाश बताते हैं. इसी को ध्यान में रखते हुए और बदमाशों की खौफ को कम करने के लिए मात्र 1 रुपए का इनाम घोषित किया गया है.

लश्कर-ए-तैयबा का आतंकी सलमान को रवांडा से भारत लाई NIA

NIA ने आतंकी गतिविधियों में शामिल शख्स सलमान रहमान खान को इंटरपोल चैनलों के जरिए रवांडा से भारत वापस लाया. केंद्रीय अन्वेषण ब्यूरो (सीबीआई) के ग्लोबल ऑपरेशन्स सेन्टर ने आतंकवाद से जुड़े मामलों में सलमान रहमान खान की रवांडा से भारत वापसी के लिए एनआईए एवं इंटरपोल राष्ट्रीय केंद्रीय ब्यूरो-किगाली (Kigali) के साथ कोऑर्डिनेट किया है.

राष्ट्रीय जांच एजेंसी ने आपराधिक षड़यंत्र, आतंकवादी संगठन का सदस्य होने और आतंकवादी संगठन को सहायता प्रदान करने से साथ-साथ शस्त्र व विस्फोटक पदार्थ अधिनियम से संबंधित अपराधों में दोषी पाया गया है. अंतर्राष्ट्रीय स्तर पर प्रतिबंधित आतंकवादी संगठन लश्कर-ए-तैयबा (एलईटी) का सदस्य होने के कारण इसने बेंगलुरु शहर में आतंकवादी गतिविधियों को आगे बढ़ाने हेतु हथियार, गोला-बारूद एवं विस्फोटक उपलब्ध कराने में सहायता की थी. बेंगलुरु शहर के हेब्बल पुलिस स्टेशन में एक एफआईआर भी दर्ज की गई थी.

देश के पूरे रेल नेटवर्क में कवच 6 सालों के अंदर इंस्टॉल हो जाएगा. बहुत तेजी से और बाकी देशों की तुलना में सबसे कम लागत में कवच सिस्टम लगाया जा रहा है. भारतीय रेलवे बहुत जल्द जीरो ट्रेन एक्सिडेंट और जीरो ट्रेन डिरेलमेंट के नए कीर्तिमान को छू लेगा. ये बात मंगलवार को रेल मंत्री अश्विनी वैष्णव ने कही. उन्होंने कहा, भारतीय रेलवे के एक लोकोमोटिव इंजन में कवच-4 इंस्टॉल करने में सिर्फ 22 घंटा का समय लगता है. यही काम पहले कई दिनों में होता था. अभी रेलवे देश की 68 लोकोमोटिव मेंटेनेंस वर्कशॉप में कवच-4 को इंस्टॉल करने का काम कर रहा है. देशभर में रोजाना 200 लोकोमोटिव ट्रेन के इंजन में कवच सिस्टम लगाया जा रहा है.

CBD For Fibromyalgia 👇🏽

Fibromyalgia is a collection of symptoms of which the most commonly reported is widespread pain. 

Research into CBD’s benefits is still new, but early studies show promising results. This is especially true for issues like sleep, anxiety, and pain.

CBD can interact with your ECS. When they do, research tells us the ECS sends out signals that work to decrease inflammation and reduce feelings of pain and discomfort. Both of these benefits could help people with fibromyalgia. #fibromyalgia 

Research on CBD benefits:

Chronic pain - A 2018 research review reported that CBD may be able to treat chronic pain, such as what people with fibromyalgia experience.

Sleep quality - A small 2019 study found that people who took CBD daily reported better sleep and less anxiety.

Depression - Another 2018 research review found that CBD usage may benefit conditions like depression, which do occur in people with fibromyalgia frequently.

How CBD can help with Anxiety 🧘‍♀️

Did you know in any given week in the UK, 8 in 10 people suffer from some form of Anxiety or Depression. 

CBD interacts with CB1 and CB2 receptors. These receptors are mostly found in the central nervous system. 

CBD works to alleviate symptoms of anxiety and depression by binding to one of the main receptors within the ECS, the CB1 receptor.

CBD is thought to positively influence the processes that regulate our mood, sleep, and pain perception, among others. These processes need to function properly, so we feel better, sleep more soundly, and experience less pain. Anxiety and depression are conditions related to poor sleep, pain, and poor mood regulation because the endocannabinoid system isn’t working to the best of its ability.

Here they are ↓

Hygiene is good. Toxic products sold to you by companies that have no idea what they are giving to people is not good.

Keep your nails clean, wash yourself and moisturise with natural products. Brush your hair. You don’t need to do much more.

True beauty and health comes from the inside and you have to avoid chemicals like this in order to maximise it.

7 signs:

1️⃣ Thinning hair

🚿 Shampoos packed with harsh chemicals will lead to hair loss. If you notice hair thinning more than usual, look at what you’re applying to your scalp.

2️⃣ Skin irritations

🧴 Are you experiencing random breakouts, dry patches, or redness? Body washes and facial cleansers are full of synthetic chemicals even if they claim ‘natural origin’.

3️⃣ Gut microbiome disruption

🦠 Harsh antibacterial agents disrupt your gut health.

4️⃣ Weakened nails

💅 If your nails are brittle or cracking, reconsider the hand soaps and nail care products you use. Many contain chemicals that weaken nails over time.

5️⃣ Hormonal imbalances

🔄 Chemicals disrupt the endocrine system, manifesting as mood swings or irregular cycles.

6️⃣ Chronic fatigue

😴 Overexposure to chemicals will inevitably lead to fatigue.

7️⃣ Premature ageing

🕰️ Heavy use of makeup and anti-aging products can actually accelerate the signs of ageing due to the harsh chemicals they contain. Sorry but your anti-aging routine might backfire.

Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez is poised to become the top Democrat on the House Oversight Committee, punctuating a huge generational shift in the party’s power center amid a sudden overthrow of senior leaders.

AOC, 35, and Rep. Gerry Connolly, 74, have been canvassing the entire Democratic Caucus for the leadership position. But according to interviews with a dozen members and staffers, AOC has earned the support of the majority of Dems on the panel – which is stacked with younger, more progressive members – though it’s the Steering and Policy Committee and the full caucus who ultimately decide.

AOC’s sudden rise in the ranks illustrates that the party’s previous concerns about younger members biding their time are waning. Dems driving that shift say they want new leadership that can fight the incoming administration of Donald Trump.

“She’s a very effective messenger, and that’s kind of the conclusion people have drawn from this election — that we haven’t had effective messengers,” said Rep. Judy Chu (D-Calif.), a senior member of the caucus.
 
Link in bio for more.

Senate Republicans have discussed elevating Sen. John Cornyn to chair of the Intel Committee, according to party officials. The move would hand Cornyn a prized gavel as consolation for losing his GOP leader bid and could help induce him to run for reelection in two years.

The complication, and almost certain deal-breaker: Cornyn would have to leapfrog the next Republican in line, Sen. Tom Cotton, writes our politics bureau chief Jonathan Martin in his latest column. And Cotton has privately made clear to Cornyn that he would claim the position.

Martin continues: “I’m told the Arkansan has already started hiring staff and refused to be coaxed into letting Cornyn take the chair... Cornyn approached Cotton to take his temperature about the post last month after the leader race, I’m told by a Republican senator, and Cotton responded by saying: ‘I’m going to be the chairman.’”

Read Martin’s latest column at the link in @politicomag’s bio.

Speaker Mike Johnson has only nine working days left for lawmakers to figure out government funding before the shutdown deadline — and he’ll almost certainly need House Dems’ support to pass it.

Congress will likely pass a stopgap government funding measure before Dec. 20 to fund the government until March 2025 at its current levels. But given Johnson’s razor-thin margin – plus conservatives in his conference who tend to oppose short-term funding fixes– House Dems will likely be the ones to get it over the finish line.

Typically, punting a funding deadline into a new year when Republicans will control every lever of power would make Dems shudder. This time, they’re not putting up much of a fight, but they have made one main demand clear for the stopgap: a robust supplemental package for disaster aid. More on how those negotiations could unfold at the link in bio. 

📷 Francis Chung/POLITICO

“Wicked” has taken over pop culture. And while the movie musical is based on a play from the early 2000s, a novel written in the ‘90s and source material from the Gilded age, some people quickly concluded it was eerily made for our times. And that its shady wizard villain was just like Donald Trump.

Contributing writer Joanna Weiss has another theory: The real Trump of “Wicked” is Glinda.

Ask yourself, Weiss argues: Would Trump ever be satisfied as the man behind the curtain? Glinda, on the other hand, is front and center, looking for crowd approval. She’s a rallier of cliques, a collector of acolytes, a self-adoring narcissist who cares deeply about her public image, Weiss continues.

And while Glinda isn’t technically a politician – and Oz is definitely not a democracy – she eventually finds herself at the center of Oz’s power structure, with influence over its leadership and the ear of a fawning public.

If the Wizard is an example of what it means to wield authoritarian power, Weiss writes, Glinda shows one path to building power in the first place. It’s the popularity, stupid.

Link in @politicomag’s bio for Weiss’ full argument on why the good witch is actually Wicked’s Trumpy character.

🎨 Bill Kuchman/POLITICO (source images via Getty Images and iStock)

Europe’s most powerful person for 2025: Giorgia Meloni.

In less than a decade, the Italian prime minister has gone from being dismissed as an ultranationalist kook to a figure with whom Brussels — and now Washington — can do business. And all the while, she’s been a key force on the forefront of a wave that is dragging European politics toward the far right.

Since her election in 2022, Meloni has introduced policies on issues like migration and LGBTQ+ rights that would once have drawn condemnation from the EU in years before. But now, the reaction from the bloc’s leaders has ranged from indifference to approval, with many accepting her as the palatable representative of the ever-more-radical zeitgeist blossoming on both sides of the Atlantic.

This is why we ranked her at the top of our annual POLITICO 28 list of the doers, dreamers and disrupters driving European politics and policy for the year ahead.

Head to the link in @politicoeurope’s bio to read our full profile of her — and see who else we included in our Class of 2025.

After being extinct in the wild for over 20 years, 5 ‘alalā raised by San Diego Zoo Wildlife Alliance have been released on Maui for the first time ever. 🐦‍⬛ 

Known as the Hawaiian crow, these remarkable birds are essential to their ecosystems, and hold a special place in Hawaiian culture as ʻaumākua, or ancestral guardians. Their introduction is a symbol of resilience, and this success gives hope for the future of the ʻalalā, their forest home, and for the people of Hawaiʻi. 

Soar to the link in our bio to learn more about this extraordinary species, and how collaborative conservation efforts are reconnecting Hawaiʻi with its native wildlife.

Important Scam Alert:
We want to warn you about a recent scam targeting job seekers using the name of one of our employees, Angela Tomaso. Please read carefully to protect yourself.

Details of the Scam:

 - Victims have reported receiving unsolicited text messages claiming to be from Angela Tomaso regarding a remote job opportunity.

 - The scammer asks for personal information to "proceed with the role" and escalates by requiring payment for a credit check as part of the process.

Note: Angela Tomaso is a valued member of our HR team, but she is NOT involved in hiring or offering roles to candidates.

To protect yourself, remember - 

Our recruiters will NEVER:
 - Ask for protected information (age, gender, etc.)
 - Request personal details or payments via informal platforms (text, Facebook Messenger, Google Hangouts, WhatsApp, Telegram)
 - Ask you to buy gift cards, pay for equipment, or send money upfront
 - Use email addresses outside of our official domains

Our recruiters will ALWAYS:
 - Contact you via email from a legitimate domain: “https://ow.ly/gywz50Uu8Ia,” “https://ow.ly/4bhV50Uu8Ii,” or “https://ow.ly/FVfj50Uu8I9”
 - Treat you with professionalism and respect
 - Properly onboard you through secure measures without requiring any upfront payments

If you receive a suspicious message or suspect fraudulent activity:
 -  Do not engage or send money
 - Report the scam to us immediately at scamalert@beaconhillstaffing.com

Stay alert, stay informed and protect yourself from scams!

What Ami Colé products HAVE to make it in the purse?

Inching towards the new year and wining down the bustle.

It’s Diarrha - @byamicole founder-  here. As I count down the days to the new year I can’t help but to be reflective and still. 2024 brought in a lot - a lot of challenges, tremendous joys, and unbelievable milestones. This brand was a brain child from a “regular” girl from Harlem with deep roots in #Senegal where my parents emigrated from in the late ‘80s. Growing up it was almost an act of rebellion to truly embrace your skin in its natural state. Everything around me (at least outside of #Harlem) told me that dark skin was the “worse case scenario” and that assimilation was just the name of the game. I’m so honored and proud to have had my community (family, friends, my mother’s salon clients) who fueled me with information and the tools I need to look in the mirror and see beauty. 

It’s still a pinch me experience to bring the beauty products, cultural experiences, and thumb-stopping campaign images like this one shot by @tala_niang for @guiss__guiss in #Dakar, #Senegal to the center stage. Let’s have the conversation. Let’s continue to show the world that beautiful doesn’t look one way. It’s okay to pair down to see YOU and love YOU. 

From the bottom of my heart, thank you for choosing me and allowing me to do this work. Thank you for giving us the life and energy to bring #AmiColeIRL to the center stage and change the narrative so that future “little girls from Harlem” and beyond can have a seat at the beautiful, diverse, fun table. We are just getting started.

Cheers to us. Cheers to you. 

Love your beauty captain,
@diarrhaxo

In today’s digital world, many people experience “popcorn brain,” a state where scattered thoughts and fragmented attention dominate their mental landscape. This condition often results from constant interaction with social media and digital devices, leading to rapid shifts in focus that make it challenging to concentrate on a single task. 

To combat this phenomenon, individuals can take several proactive steps. Establishing boundaries for screen time, practicing mindfulness, and engaging in activities that require sustained attention—like reading or deep work—can help restore cognitive balance. By prioritizing mental well-being and intentionally creating space for focused, undistracted thought, we can counteract the effects of popcorn brain and improve our overall productivity and quality of life. 

#Emeritus #MentalWellbeing

A Heartfelt Thank You to Luce Coffee Roasters!
We’re incredibly grateful to Luce Coffee Roasters in Houston for their unwavering support of our project to empower coffee farmers like Arlin Andino, the owner of Finca Esquipulas in Nicaragua.
Their dedication to sustainability and exceptional coffee shines through in every cup. By showcasing Arlin’s incredible coffees at their café, Luce Coffee Roasters is helping to make a real difference—ensuring farmers receive fair compensation while bringing world-class coffee to their customers.

Together, we’re building a brighter future for coffee farmers and fostering a sustainable coffee industry. Thank you, Luke and Helen,  for being an incredible partner in this journey!

Try these 3 quick, tasty and affordable sides this Thanksgiving 🦃📕Shop Target for all ingredients 🛒

🌿Honey rosemary whipped feta dip🌿
8oz block feta cheese 
2/3 cup plain greek yogurt 
2 tablespoons honey 
2 tablespoons olive oil 
1 teaspoon dried rosemary 
kosher salt to taste 
Chopped walnuts and honey, for topping (optional) 

Add the feta, yogurt, honey, oil, rosemary, and salt to a food processor. blend on high speed until completely smooth, about 60 seconds. 

🌟Roasted brussels sprouts salad🌟 
1 pound shaved brussels sprouts (roasted with olive oil, kosher salt, & black pepper for 15 min at 400 degrees F) 
5 cups shredded kale 
1.5 cups cooked quinoa 
1 honey crisp apple, diced 
1/2 cup crumbled goat cheese 
1/2 cup pomegranate arils 
1/2 cup chopped walnuts 

tahini dressing: 
1/4 cup tahini 
2 tablespoons olive oil 
2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar 
2 tablespoons dijon mustard 
2 tablespoons honey 
juice of 1 lemon 
1 teaspoon kosher salt 
1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper 
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 

whisk all dressing ingredients until combined. add all salad ingredients to a large mixing bowl, then toss with the dressing until coated.

Maryam Nassirzadeh once defined how downtown girls wanted to dress. Her brand, Maryam Nassir Zadeh (with the spelling of her last name tweaked), makes clothes that are simple, often skimpy, and meant to be piled on — fluttery cardigans shrugged over bikini tops, dresses over pants, leather jackets over slips, and wide belts cinched anywhere from upper ribs to hipbone. A typical MNZ outfit looks like it was fished out of a carry-on because you just got back from Ibiza and you’re off to Hydra next week. 

New York used to be a real shopping town. When MNZ opened, it joined independent boutiques all over downtown and gentrified Brooklyn where you could go find clothes you had never seen before. But below all this brick and mortar ran an algorithmic stream, and around 2017, it began to erode the foundations. In 2000, Net-a-Porter was founded. Then SSENSE. Then Farfetch. Department stores stepped up their e-commerce. And all of these websites did crazy, unbeatable sales. Smaller stores just could not compete. MNZ was more protected, at least for a while, but the seams were visible if you were looking for them. By 2021, Nassirzadeh admitted to Vogue that MNZ had been struggling to cover the cost of new samples for its clothes. Now, it’s a mystery how the brand survives at all. But for the first time this year, MNZ did something many of her peers would have done long ago: collaborated with big brands like J.Crew. At the link in bio, features writer Madeline Leung Coleman delves into the rise and fall of Maryam Nassir Zadeh, and the brand’s current efforts to rise yet again.

Provecho started with the desire of 2 not so young kids (me and Bruno) to score perfect waves in a remote place, getting away from the tour rush and crowds, to go enjoy the simplicity of a surf trip. With no schedule, not many people around, score perfect empty lineups, eat good food, and make memories. Provecho means to enjoy, take advantage, benefit, and, in this case, benefit from an opportunity. We had about a 1-month gap in our schedule and endless destinations to choose from. We ended up choosing what you’re about to watch, and yes, we took a good provecho of that moment and enjoyed another trip for the books. Hope you enjoy it as well.

The Skin Microbiome by @dr_mariedrago ⚡️

✨ What is the skin microbiome?
It refers to all microbes and micro-organisms that live on the skin. Skin is not sterile, and that’s a good thing!

✨ What does it do?
It’s your first line of defence and it helps your immune system so it’s great to soothe sensitive skin.
Most of those bacteria are good bacteria: 95% of them help you & support your immune system. Sometimes, there are bad bacteria like the one responsible for eczema (staphylococcus aureus) or acne (cutibacterium acnes).

✨ What we do at Gallinée is support those good bacteria to help control the bad ones. We do that thanks to prebiotics, probiotics and postbiotics that help you having the best skin possible.

After weeks of bombardment from the Houthis in Yemen, the IDF said enough is enough and has now taken off the gloves. 

Israel has confirmed that it launched widespread attacks across Yemen in response to the Houthi’s terror. 

This is the beginning of an ongoing campaign to stop the firing of drones and ballistic missiles into Israel. 

So far, the results of Israel’s attack in Yemen:
 
1. Sana’a Airport – Completely shut down.
2. Power Plants in Sana’a – Destroyed.
3. Hodeidah Seaport – Shut down once again.

This is all happening during the press conference of the Houthi leader.

Attacks at the airport include the control tower, planes, and runways, were attacked, resulting in several casualties. 

Israel is expecting the Houthis to intensify their attacks now on Israel but the Israeli leadership said this is the beginning of a long operation. 

Is this the beginning of the end of the Houthi’s? Let’s hope so.

This is Aviel’s mechina, which is where they prepare the guys for the army, physically and spiritually. The name of the school is Eli and sadly, they’ve lost many graduates in the war. Here they are singing asking Hashem to open the gates of heaven and hear our prayers. So beautiful.
What an incredible shot. Talk about turning darkness into light! 🙏🇮🇱💪✡️❤️🔥

Happy Hanukkah, Houthis! 

When we say that this is the holiday of lights, we mean it. 

Candles aren’t the only thing we’re lighting up this Hanukah. 

You might not know it yet, but you’ll soon find out that you messed with the wrong country! 💪🇮🇱✡️🙏🔥💥

IDF Official Statement on Houthi strike: 

“In accordance with plans approved by the Chief of Staff, the Minister of Defense, and the Prime Minister, Israeli Air Force fighter jets recently carried out targeted strikes, guided by intelligence, against key assets of the Houthi terrorist regime along Yemen’s western coast and deeper inland.

The Houthi regime has persistently attacked Israel and its citizens, launching drones and surface-to-surface missiles into the country.

Key targets included infrastructure used by the Houthis for military activities at Sana’a International Airport, as well as the Aziz and Ras Qantib power stations, which serve as critical components of the regime’s electrical grid. Additionally, strikes were carried out on facilities at the ports of Hodeidah, Al-Salif, and Ras Qantib.

These sites were utilized for transferring Iranian weapons and facilitating the arrival of senior Iranian officials, highlighting the Houthis’ exploitation of civilian infrastructure for terrorist operations.

The Houthi regime is a pivotal arm of Iran’s regional axis, responsible for destabilizing the region and threatening global maritime freedom. Operating as an independent terrorist entity with Iranian backing, the Houthis continue to pose a significant threat to Israel and its citizens.

The IDF reaffirms its commitment to act decisively against threats to Israel, regardless of distance.”

✔️ Enabling multi-factor authentication (MFA)
✔️ Backing up your files and data
✔️ Adopting a Zero Trust policy
